OL,3,CUS issues arrest warrant against
OL,4,CIndia's richest billionaire for fraud
OL,6,FThe US Attorney's Office for the
OL,7,FEastern District of New York said the
OL,8,Ftycoon and his co-defendants sought to
OL,9,F"obtain and finance massive state
OL,10,Fenergy supply contracts through
OL,11,Fcorruption and fraud at the expense of
OL,12,FUS investors,
OL,14,FUS Attorney Breon Peace added the
OL,15,Fdefendants "orchestrated an elaborate
OL,16,Fscheme" and wanted to "enrich
OL,17,Fthemselves at the expense of the
OL,18,Fintegrity of our financial markets."
